      • registerNotifications

        public boolean registerNotifications()

        Returns:

        See Also:
        registerNotifications(boolean)

      • registerNotifications

        public boolean registerNotifications(boolean usePolling)
        Registers the TS3 notifications for receiving text messages and basic user notifications. This method is a convenience method for registering all the text message notifications. It also spawns a polling thread that polls for the following events:
        • User connected
        • User disconnected
        • User moved

        A polling thread is necessary to check if users move channels, as the TS3 Server Query "channel" notifications only notifies if a user moves in or out of the channel that the query client resides.

        If usePolling is false, then the default "server" and "channel" notifications are registered in place of the polling thread.

        Parameters:
        usePolling - Whether or not to spawn a polling thread
        Returns:
        True if all the notifications were successfully registered.
